H0.text: What was Queen Victoria's first Christian name. Adelaide

H1.text: What was Queen Victoria's first Christian name. Georgiana

H2.text: What was Queen Victoria's first Christian name. Charlotte

H3.text: What was Queen Victoria's first Christian name. Alexandrina

A4.text: Official documents prepared on the first day of her reign described her as Alexandrina Victoria, but the first name was withdrawn at her own wish and not used again.

A5.text: Additional names proposed by her parents—Georgina (or Georgiana), Charlotte, and Augusta—were dropped on the instructions of the Prince Regent.
